    "system": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<p><em>You either smear a drop of pitch on your hands or step on a piece of brittle coal as you imagine darkness spreading into the area you can see. All light fails to penetrate the black wispy globe the spell creates, which looks like a thick cloud of smoke.</em></p><p><strong>Area Hazard</strong> </p><ul><li><p>You create darkness that cannot be seen through even by creatures with &amp;reference[darkvision]. This magical darkness spreads arounds corners.</p></li><li><p>Non-magic light can't spread through the darkness.</p></li><li><p>If this spell overlaps with an area of light created by a spell of 1st level or lower*, the spell that created the light is dispelled.</p></li><li><p>If the point you choose is an object you are holding or one that is being worn or carried the darkness is exuded by the object and moves with it.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>*Upcasting:</strong> The level of light-creating spell Darkness can dispel increases by 1 for each spell level above 2nd level.</p>",
            "chat": "<strong>Area Hazard</strong> </p><ul><li><p>You create darkness that cannot be seen through even by creatures with &amp;reference[darkvision]. This magical darkness spreads arounds corners.</p></li><li><p>Non-magic light can't spread through the darkness.</p></li><li><p>If this spell overlaps with an area of light created by a spell of 1st level or lower*, the spell that created the light is dispelled.</p></li><li><p>If the point you choose is an object you are holding or one that is being worn or carried the darkness is exuded by the object and moves with it.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>*Upcasting:</strong> The level of light-creating spell Darkness can dispel increases by 1 for each spell level above 2nd level.</p>"
        },
